21/09/2009
DAMASCUS, Syria -- The Interior Ministry announced on Saturday (September 19th) that it has removed all visa requirements for holders of Turkish passports who spend up to 90 days visiting. The decision became effective on Friday. Earlier in the week, Turkish Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu and Syrian counterpart Walid al-Muallem announced they had reached an agreement to remove visas for citizens travelling between their countries, in an effort to boost economic integration. (Anadolu news agency, Xinhua AFP - 19/09/09)
